.TH HEXDUMP 1 "2025" "Nightingale" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hexdump \- display file contents in hexadecimal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hexdump
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hexdump
reads data from standard input and displays it in hexadecimal format
with both hex values and ASCII representation.
.PP
The output format shows:
.IP \(bu 3
Offset in hexadecimal on the left
.IP \(bu
16 bytes per line in hex in the middle
.IP \(bu
ASCII representation on the right (non-printable characters shown as dots)
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B hexdump < file.bin
Display the hex dump of file.bin.
.TP
.B cat /bin/ls | hexdump
Show the hex representation of the ls binary.
.TP
.B echo "Hello" | hexdump
Display the hex values of "Hello".
.SH NOTES
Unlike traditional
.BR hexdump
or
.BR hd ,
this command:
.IP \(bu 3
Only reads from standard input (no file arguments)
.IP \(bu
Does not support format strings
.IP \(bu
Always uses 16-byte-wide output
.SH OUTPUT FORMAT
.EX
00000000  48 65 6c 6c 6f 20 57 6f  72 6c 64 0a              |Hello World.|
.EE
